        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/local/northam-seeks-to-delay-skill-games-ban-tax-profits-for-covid-19-fund-put-off/article_4b67e654-9e01-5f20-97c7-2d3b68ea991a.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Northam seeks to delay skill games ban, tax profits for COVID-19 fund; put off minimum wage hike</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">BY MICHAEL MARTZ
Richmond Times-Dispatch</span></li><li class="card-date"><span class="text-muted">Updated </span><time datetime="2020-04-12T17:25:12-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Apr 12, 2020</time>
    </li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/local/northam-seeks-to-delay-skill-games-ban-tax-profits-for-covid-19-fund-put-off/article_4b67e654-9e01-5f20-97c7-2d3b68ea991a.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Gov. Ralph Northam will propose to delay a ban on electronic skill games for a year, tax their profits and use the money for a COVID-19 response fund to help small businesses, protect people's housing and support nursing homes and other health care providers.</p></p>
                            </div>
                        
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    
