        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/state/federal-courts-continue-operations-through-pandemic/article_670c538b-27b9-5d30-a2b8-39f1cec6d9b1.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Federal courts continue operations through pandemic</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span id="author-409fd64e-f003-11e7-a5ae-3b6be71044b5-asset-670c538b-27b9-5d30-a2b8-39f1cec6d9b1" class="tnt-byline asset-byline"  >By TYLER HAMMEL
thammel@dailyprogress.com </p><p>(434) 978-7268 </span>
                </li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-04-12T16:15:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Apr 12, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/state/federal-courts-continue-operations-through-pandemic/article_670c538b-27b9-5d30-a2b8-39f1cec6d9b1.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Though telephonic hearings have often been used for civil hearings in Virginia’s Western U.S. District Courts this month due to the constitutional right to a speedy trial, some criminal hearings have begun to use virtual means as well.</p></p>
                            </div>
                        
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="clearfix"></div>
        </article>
                    
                </div>
            
