        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/local/death-count-now-at-32-at-canterbury-as-covid-symptoms-spread/article_672f4b28-4769-551f-bf12-f36e61b999ed.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Death count now at 32 at Canterbury as COVID symptoms spread</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">By MICHAEL MARTZ
Richmond Times-Dispatch </span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-04-07T14:05:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Apr 7, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/local/death-count-now-at-32-at-canterbury-as-covid-symptoms-spread/article_672f4b28-4769-551f-bf12-f36e61b999ed.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Four more residents of Canterbury Rehabilitation &amp; Healthcare Center have died of COVID-19 in the past day, bringing the death toll to 32 as the skilled nursing center in western Henrico County approaches the total fatalities at a Seattle-area nursing home where the coronavirus first erupted in the United States.</p></p>
