        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/local/virginia-senate-plans-to-convene-at-science-museum-during-april-veto-session/article_524d7996-68d0-5b96-86a1-2006192ad9f7.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Virginia Senate plans to convene at Science Museum during April veto session</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">By JEFF E. SCHAPIRO
Richmond Times-Dispatch
</span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-04-06T17:10:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Apr 6, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/local/virginia-senate-plans-to-convene-at-science-museum-during-april-veto-session/article_524d7996-68d0-5b96-86a1-2006192ad9f7.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>To help protect members and staff from COVID-19, the Virginia Senate will trade its clubby confines at the state Capitol for the state science museum when the legislature returns to Richmond for its spring session April 22.</p></p>
