                </div>
            
            
        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/state/virginias-coronavirus-stay-at-home-order-what-is-and-is-not-allowed/article_5d61f28f-aeb1-592e-9b9d-1e5e52534ef5.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Virginia's coronavirus stay-at-home order: What is and is not allowed</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">richmond Times-Dispatch </span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-03-30T14:19:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Mar 30, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/state/virginias-coronavirus-stay-at-home-order-what-is-and-is-not-allowed/article_5d61f28f-aeb1-592e-9b9d-1e5e52534ef5.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>On Monday afternoon, Virginia Gov. Ralph Northam issued Executive Order 55, which is a temporary stay-at-home order, due to the novel coronavirus pandemic.</p></p>
