        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/state/uva-pharmacist-others-report-growing-demand-for-experimental-covid-19-medications/article_6dafd178-ac45-5f93-bec8-bf9453882e6c.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            UVa pharmacist, others report growing demand for experimental COVID-19 medications</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">By KATE MASTERS
The Virginia Mercury </span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-03-27T19:45:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Mar 27, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/state/uva-pharmacist-others-report-growing-demand-for-experimental-covid-19-medications/article_6dafd178-ac45-5f93-bec8-bf9453882e6c.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>On Wednesday, Virginia Health Commissioner Dr. Norman Oliver <a href="http://www.vdh.virginia.gov/clinicians/treatment-of-covid-19/" target="_blank">issued a letter</a> warning of a “surge in demand” for medications commonly used to treat malaria, lupus, rheumatoid arthritis, HIV and other conditions.</p></p>
