                <div class="card-body"><div class="card-labels">
            
                <div class="card-label-section text-muted">
                    <a href="/news/state/" class="tnt-section-tag">State</a>
                </div>
            
            
        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/state/va-localities-to-state-delay-minimum-wage-increase-other-unfunded-mandates-but-protect-k-12/article_6fe979c8-6241-53e3-adbf-350b0731f91e.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Va. localities to state: delay minimum wage increase, other unfunded mandates, but protect K-12 funding</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">BY MICHAEL MARTZ
Richmond Times-Dispatch</span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-03-27T15:45:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Mar 27, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/state/va-localities-to-state-delay-minimum-wage-increase-other-unfunded-mandates-but-protect-k-12/article_6fe979c8-6241-53e3-adbf-350b0731f91e.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Virginia's local governments say they face economic calamity unless the state delays new legislation - including an increase in the minimum wage, permission to allow collective bargaining for local government employees and expanded eligibility for workers' compensation - that the General Assembly enacted this year before the coronavirus pandemic shut down many businesses and put thousands of Virginians out of work.</p></p>
                            </div>
                        
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="clearfix"></div>
        </article>
                    
                </div>
            
