        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/state/virginia-offers-flexibility-so-high-school-seniors-can-still-graduate/article_79004ed9-c49c-54e5-a809-c31f5128d7c9.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Virginia offers flexibility so high school seniors can still graduate</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">By JUSTIN MATTINGLY
Richmond Times-Dispatch </span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-03-24T10:30:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Mar 24, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/state/virginia-offers-flexibility-so-high-school-seniors-can-still-graduate/article_79004ed9-c49c-54e5-a809-c31f5128d7c9.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Guidance from the Virginia Department of Education released after Gov. Ralph Northam ordered state schools to be closed for the rest of the school year provides leniency so members of the senior class can still graduate.</p></p>
                            </div>
                        
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    
