        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/state/this-is-going-to-be-a-big-challenge-census-count-goes-on-amid-covid-19/article_da2f3555-ad07-5161-92b3-228d001de034.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            'This is going to be a big challenge': Census count goes on amid COVID-19</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">By MEL LEONOR Richmond Times-Dispatch </span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-03-22T17:00:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Mar 22, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/state/this-is-going-to-be-a-big-challenge-census-count-goes-on-amid-covid-19/article_da2f3555-ad07-5161-92b3-228d001de034.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>As of Saturday afternoon, <a href="https://2020census.gov/en/response-rates.html" target="_blank">19.2% of Virginians had completed their census form</a>, either online, via mail or by phone, according to data published by the U.S. Census Bureau. </p></p>
                            </div>
                        
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    
