        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/archives/virginia-abc-allowing-all-restaurants-with-on-premises-licenses-to-sell-wine-and-beer-to/article_ed2f9b61-cb27-5b78-babe-6d9603776bd0.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Virginia ABC allowing all restaurants with on-premises licenses to sell wine and beer to go. Could cocktails be next?</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">By KARRI PEIFER
Richmond Times-Dispatch
</span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-03-20T17:50:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Mar 20, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/archives/virginia-abc-allowing-all-restaurants-with-on-premises-licenses-to-sell-wine-and-beer-to/article_ed2f9b61-cb27-5b78-babe-6d9603776bd0.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Any restaurant in Virginia with a valid license to sell wine and beer on-premises can now sell wine and beer to go and for delivery without applying for additional permits.</p></p>
