        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/state/virginia-looking-to-cancel-state-sol-testing-amid-coronavirus-pandemic/article_3008037a-e79b-5c9f-9ecb-cf975fbbc850.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Virginia looking to cancel state SOL testing amid coronavirus pandemic</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">By JUSTIN MATTINGLY
Richmond Times-Dispatch </span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-03-17T16:00:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Mar 17, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/state/virginia-looking-to-cancel-state-sol-testing-amid-coronavirus-pandemic/article_3008037a-e79b-5c9f-9ecb-cf975fbbc850.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Virginia's education leaders want to cancel the state's Standards of Learning testing this year as schools remain closed in response to the spread of the coronavirus.</p></p>
                            </div>
                        
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    
