        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/uva/uva-moving-online-and-canceling-in-person-classes-for-the-foreseeable-future/article_53d23437-1d98-52dd-8128-747f096d3fa4.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            UVa moving online and canceling in-person classes 'for the foreseeable future'</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span id="author-800d620a-9406-11e7-b6e1-7bb976dafedf-asset-53d23437-1d98-52dd-8128-747f096d3fa4" class="tnt-byline asset-byline"  >By RUTH SERVEN SMITH
rserven@dailyprogress.com | (434) 978-7254 </span>
                </li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-03-11T12:47:00-04:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Mar 11, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/uva/uva-moving-online-and-canceling-in-person-classes-for-the-foreseeable-future/article_53d23437-1d98-52dd-8128-747f096d3fa4.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Wednesday afternoon, the university sent a memo to students, staff and faculty that no classes would be held Grounds "for the foreseeable future, quite possibly through the end of the semester," as the country and Virginia battle the novel coronavirus. </p></p>
