        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/state/virginia-braces-for-a-possible-coronavirus-outbreak/article_ac5dfbcf-f4a4-52b4-9f9f-077b40c45bdb.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Virginia braces for a possible coronavirus outbreak</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">By BRIDGET BALCH
Richmond Times-Dispatch
</span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-02-28T17:50:00-05:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Feb 28, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/state/virginia-braces-for-a-possible-coronavirus-outbreak/article_ac5dfbcf-f4a4-52b4-9f9f-077b40c45bdb.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Amid the continued spread of coronavirus across the globe and warnings that a disruptive outbreak is likely to hit the U.S., Virginia’s health department, hospitals, schools and universities are preparing for a potential public health crisis.</p></p>
                            </div>
                        
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    
