                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span id="author-800d620a-9406-11e7-b6e1-7bb976dafedf-asset-a604fe01-c172-5cbc-8191-61fb265250be" class="tnt-byline asset-byline"  >By RUTH SERVEN SMITH
rserven@dailyprogress.com
(434) 978-7254 </span>
                </li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-01-31T13:45:00-05:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Jan 31, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/state/two-more-potential-coronavirus-cases-in-virginia-being-investigated/article_a604fe01-c172-5cbc-8191-61fb265250be.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Two more people in Virginia are being investigated as potential cases of novel coronavirus, according to the Virginia Department of Health, bringing the total of such investigations in the state to five.</p></p>
                            </div>
                        
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    
                </div>
            </div>
            <div class="clearfix"></div>
        </article>
                    
                </div>
            
                <div class="collection-card">
                    
                        <article id="card-summary-eb7987ad-4ecc-50b5-8cf7-1ad9d43842ca" class="clearfix card summary   tnt-section-news tnt-sub-section-local">
            <div class="card-container">
                
                <div class="card-body"><div class="card-labels">
            
                <div class="card-label-section text-muted">
                    <a href="/news/local/" class="tnt-section-tag">Local News</a>
                </div>
            
            
                <div class="card-label-flags">
                    <span class="tnt-flag label label-flag label-flag-default label-flag-top-story">top story</span> 
                </div>
            
        </div><div class="card-headline"><h3 class="tnt-headline ">
        
             <a href="/news/local/two-of-three-suspected-carriers-of-coronavirus-in-va-test-negative-uva-says-threat-is/article_eb7987ad-4ecc-50b5-8cf7-1ad9d43842ca.html" class="tnt-asset-link">
        

        
            Two of three suspected carriers of coronavirus in Va. test negative; UVa says threat is low</a></h3></div><div class="card-meta">
            <ul class="list-inline">
                        <li class="card-byline text-muted"><span  class="tnt-byline">By SABRINA MORENO
Richmond Times-Dispatch </span></li><li class="card-date">
        <time datetime="2020-01-27T17:00:00-05:00" class="tnt-date asset-date text-muted">Jan 27, 2020</time></li><li class="card-comment-count"><a href="/news/local/two-of-three-suspected-carriers-of-coronavirus-in-va-test-negative-uva-says-threat-is/article_eb7987ad-4ecc-50b5-8cf7-1ad9d43842ca.html#comments" class="cm" title="0 comments"><span class="fas tnt-comments"></span> <span class="count">0</span></a></li></ul>
        </div>
                    
                    
                    
                    
                        
                        
                            <div class="card-lead">
                                <p class="tnt-summary"><p>Two of three possible cases of the coronavirus respiratory outbreak under review by the Virginia Department of Health tested negative on Monday.</p></p>
                            </div>
                        
                    
                    
                    
                    
                    
                </div>
